  #contribute.modal.fade(role='dialog')
    .modal-dialog.modal-lg
      .modal-content
        .modal-header
          button.close(type='button', data-dismiss='modal') ×
          h4.modal-title Want To Contribute?
        .modal-body
          p Want to contribute and make this site even better? Check out the source code at <a href="https://github.com/baseballlover723/pokemon-go-dps">https://github.com/baseballlover723/pokemon-go-dps</a>.
          p Specifics on how you can help this website grow are in the README.
          p If you aren't familiar with Javascript, then it will probably be difficult (not impossible) for you to contribute this way. Don't worry too much if you can't program, let me know if you have an idea or metric you want to see on this site by sending me at email at <a href='mailto:baseballlover723@gmail.com?subject=Pokémon%20GO%20DPS%20Optimizer%20Feedback'>baseballlover723@gmail.com</a>! I'll let you know if I can implement your idea or metric.
        .modal-footer
          button.btn.btn-default(type='button', data-dismiss='modal') Close
  #todo-list.modal.fade(role='dialog')
    .modal-dialog.modal-lg
      .modal-content
        .modal-header
          button.close(type='button', data-dismiss='modal') ×
          h4.modal-title TODO List
        .modal-body
          p School is starting up for me soon, and I'll be busy looking for a full time job, so expect updates to come in a lot less frequently. I hope that my schedule will allow me to continue updating this site, don't worry though, even if I'm not actively updating the site, it should still update from bulbapedia if Niantic changes any moves attributes like power or duration. Though right now if Niantic updates what moves a pokemon can learn, or adds new pokemon, I still have to make a manual update, but it shouldn't be terribly hard to make that manual change, so if you notice that the site is inaccurate, send me an email at <a href='mailto:baseballlover723@gmail.com?subject=Pokémon%20GO%20DPS%20Optimizer%20Feedback'>baseballlover723@gmail.com</a> to let me know!
          br
          p TODO List, note that actual completion dates can be very different than the estimated depending on what happens irl with me, these estimates are fairly conservative though
            ul
              li <s>Factor in STAB</s> Completed: 8/1/2016
              li <s>Factor in base stats</s> Completed: 8/6/2016
              li <s>Add a tab to calculate DPS against specific Pokémon</s> Completed: 8/15/2016
              li Rework UI (Estimated competition: On Hold)
              li When calculating gym counters, consider the average typed damage that each pokemon inflicts. (Consider how resistance your attacker is to each gym defenders moveset damage distribution) (Estimated completion: On Hold)
              li Let you choose gym defenders moves (Estimated completion: On Hold)
              li Button to toggle inclusion of legendary pokemon (Estimated completion: On Hold)
              li Convert backend to use a database rather than json files (Estimated competition: On Hold)
              li Add gym defense (Estimated completion: On Hold)
              li Add gym defense with dodging assumption (Estimated Completion: On Hold)
        .modal-footer
          button.btn.btn-default(type='button', data-dismiss='modal') Close
  #change-log.modal.fade(role='dialog')
    .modal-dialog.modal-lg
      .modal-content
        .modal-header
          button.close(type='button', data-dismiss='modal') ×
          h4.modal-title Change Log
        .modal-body
          p 11/26/2016:
            ul
              li Updated base stats to reflect base stats change on 11/21/2016 (note Lapras was not updated)
          p 9/20/2016:
            ul
              li Added Legacy movesets that Niantic didn't retroactively remove.
          p 9/5/2016:
            ul
              li Sorry about not many updates lately, getting busy with school
              li Now if using your charge move is suboptimal, it won't calculate its dps with it and its charge move damage percentage will be 0%.
              li Added charge move damage percentage. Higher charge percentages show the percentage of damage that is done by the charge move in a rotation. In general, large charge damage percentages are movesets that are more susceptible to overkilling targets and wasting dps
          p 8/28/2016:
            ul
              li Updated some movesets that Niantic changed recently (in the future removed movesets will be marked and displayed).
              li Made the most recent changes be at the top of this list instead of the bottom.
          p 8/25/2016:
            ul
              li Now you can export the table to excel.
              li Added duration, which is how long it takes to do 1 iteration of quick and charge moves.
          p 8/16/2016:
            ul
              li You can now change the super effective and not very effective modifiers.
              li Added a description on how to use the gym defenders feature.
          p 8/15/2016:
            ul
              li Implemented counter matchups to gym defender(s).
          p 8/10/2016:
            ul
              li Made the rank column unsortable, evidently this is a popular column to sort, and it doesn't do anything.
          p 8/9/2016:
            ul
              li Updated the offensive rating to also take into account defense.
              li Added a column for total stats.
              li Puts estimated completion dates for the TODO list.
              li Second Update: Removed crit from DPS equations since it isn't implemented yet.
          p 8/7/2016:
            ul
              li Forgot to update the offensive rating for the fast and charge move.
              li Second update: added EPS.
              li Third update: added Adjusted DPS.
          p 8/6/2016:
            ul
              li Added STAB Offensive Rating, which takes into account the pokemon's base stats.
              li Added Column visibility options, since the table is getting hard to fit on one screen.
              li Changed my header library so now if should line up with the table correctly once you scroll down now.
          p 8/5/2016:
            ul
              li Added support for searching from the url, now you can share your searches with your friends or enemies, I'm not too picky.
              li Made the rank column show the global ranking of the row in the current sort.
        .modal-footer
            button.btn.btn-default(type='button', data-dismiss='modal') Close
